<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6986895>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Photos of Afrixalus phantasma sp. nov. in life. Adult male holotype, ZFMK 103454 (field no. JMD 723), from Gishwati-Mukura National Park, Rwanda, in the habitat showing nighttime coloration (A), adult male paratype, ZFMK 103460 (field no. JMD 679) from Kamiranzovu Swamp, Nyungwe National Park, showing daytime coloration in dorsal (B) and ventral views (C), adult male paratype UTEP 20802 (EBG 1198) from Kahuzi-Biega National Park, DRC (D), photographed the morning after capture." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6986895/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6986899>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Photos of the preserved holotype of Afrixalus phantasma sp. nov. (ZFMK 103454) in dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views (to scale), and plantar view of the left foot (C). Photos of the preserved holotype of A. lacustris sp. nov. (UTEP 20805) in dorsal (D) and ventral (E) views (to scale), and plantar view of the left foot (F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6986899/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6986901>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Audiospectrogram (top) and corresponding waveform (bottom) of a five-note advertisement call of a paratype (ZFMK 103459) of Afrixalus phantasma sp. nov. recorded on 11 March 2011 at Kamiranzovu swamp, Nyungwe National Park, Rwanda." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6986901/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6986903>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Total call length (diamonds; five-note advertisement calls only) and energy maximum of dominant frequency (triangles) of the advertisement call of Afrixalus phantasma sp. nov. at varying ambient temperatures." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6986903/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6986232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Photos of the habitat of (A) Afrixalus phantasma sp. nov. in Kamiranzovu Swamp, Nyungwe National Park, Rwanda, showing a forest edge in a montane marsh, and (B) A. lacustris sp. nov. from the vicinity of Kalundu, DRC, showing transitional forest." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6986232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6986889>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Afrixalus phantasma sp. nov. (black symbols) and A. lacustris sp. nov. (white symbols). Star, triangle, and circle symbols represent holotype, examined specimens, and literature records (Drewes & Vindum 1994; Laurent 1950, 1952, 1972, 1982; Vonesh 2001), respectively. Areas shaded in lighter gray are below 1700 meters, whereas areas shaded in darker gray are 1700 meters or higher. Lakes are shown in white. Gray triangle symbol represents A. lacustris specimens (RMCA 77-020-B-133–136) from a problematic locality at Tubutubu, Itombwe Plateau, DRC; see species account for details. B = Burundi, R = Rwanda." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6986889/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

